            <h2>The Economics of a Key: Understanding the Odds</h2>
            <p>Every standard case you open operates on the same fixed probabilities, officially disclosed by Valve. The value of a case is not determined by better odds, but by the desirability of the items within these tiers. Understand that these odds are independent for every opening; you are never "due" for a win.</p>
