        <section id="roi">
            <h2>ROI - The Trader's Compass</h2>
            <p>Return on Investment (ROI) is the single most important metric for evaluating a case. It calculates the expected return against your cost (Case Price + Key Price). An ROI below 100% signifies an expected loss over a large sample size. In this market, a <strong>65-75% ROI is considered very good.</strong> Use the calculator below to understand the relationship between cost, value, and return.</p>
            <div class="roi-calculator">
                <div class="input-group">
                    <label for="casePrice">Case Price ($)</label>
                    <input type="number" id="casePrice" value="0.57" step="0.01">
                </div>
                <div class="input-group">
                    <label for="avgValue">Avg. Item Value ($)</label>
                    <input type="number" id="avgValue" value="2.32" step="0.01">
                </div>
                 <div class="input-group">
